<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 02 at 4:44PM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southwestern McIntosh
and northwestern Pittsburg Counties through 515 PM CDT...
At 444 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms from 2
miles south of Raiford to 5 miles northwest of Haywood. Movement was
south at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.
Locations in or near the path include...
Mcalester...                      Crowder...
Canadian...                       Indianola...
Arrowhead State Park...           Raiford...
Haywood...                        Scipio...
Vivian...                         Arpelar...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
